== Prep the Ingredients ==

Preheat the oven to 450 degrees. Halve, peel, and finely dice the @yellow onion{1}(peeled and finely diced). Finely dice the @celery{1}(diced). Peel and finely dice the @carrot{6%oz}(peeled and finely diced). Mince or grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(minced). Strip the @thyme{1/4%oz} from the stems and roughly chop the leaves.

Heat @butter{2%tablespoon} in a medium #oven-proof pan{} over medium heat. Add the celery, onion, carrot, garlic, and thyme to the pan and cook for ~{8-10%minutes}, stirring occasionally, until very soft. Season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}.

== Biscuit Dough ==

Make the biscuit dough: In a medium #bowl{}, whisk together @flour{1/2%cup}, @baking powder{1 1/2%teaspoons}, @sugar{1/2%teaspoon}, and @salt{1/4%teaspoon}.

> If you have a sifter, feel free to use it here!

Gently stir in @heavy cream{1/3%cup} until a very shaggy dough forms. Sprinkle your counter with @flour{1%tablespoon}, then turn the mixture out onto the counter and briefly knead into a ball. Press into a 1-inch thick disk, wrap with @plastic wrap{}, and place in the #freezer{} to chill.

== Gravy ==

Sprinkle @flour{2%tablespoons} over the vegetables in the #pan{}. Stir to combine and cook for ~{1%minute}. Very slowly whisk @water{2%cups} and the @chicken stock concentrate{1} into the pan. Bring to a boil, then reduce to a simmer for ~{6-8%minutes}, until very thick. Taste and season with salt and pepper. Remove from heat.

> For a more decadent filling, stir the remaining @heavy cream{3 2/3%oz} into the gravy.

== Chicken ==

While the gravy simmers, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Season the @chicken breasts{12%oz} on all sides with salt and pepper. Add the chicken to the pan and cook ~{4-5%minutes} per side, until cooked through. Set aside to rest for ~{5%minutes}.

== Biscuits ==

Remove the biscuit dough from the #refrigerator{} and place onto a lightly floured surface (you can use any remaining flour for this). Lightly press into a 3/4-inch thick square. Cut into 4 quarters.

== Finish the Pot Pie ==

Dice the chicken into 1/2-inch cubes. Fold the chicken and @peas{4%oz} into the gravy.

> If you do not have an oven-proof pan, transfer the mixture to an 8x8-inch baking dish.

Top mixture with the biscuits. Bake in the #oven{} for ~{10-15%minutes}, until biscuits are puffed and golden brown. Enjoy!